'''''The Wyvern's Spur''''' is the second book of [[The Finder's Stone trilogy]] by [[Jeff Grubb]] and [[Kate Novak]].

{{quote|''More than a hunk of junk, the [[Wyvern's Spur]] has moldered in a crypt for fifteen generations... until now. The [[Wyvernspur family]]'s powerful heirloom has been stolen, and the grand wizard and patriarch [[Drone Wyvernspur]] is the first to fall to the ancient item's [[curse]]. The family fool, [[Giogioni Wyvernspur|Giogi]], is left to find it, but even recovering the spur cannot guarantee his clan's safety.''

''Fortunately, the famous halfling bard [[Olive Ruskettle]] and a mysterious and talented mage named [[Cat (person)|Cat]] are determined to help. But when betrayal and enchantment threaten Giogi's progress, he must invoke the spur's awesome might... or become its next victim!''}}
